      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Document curated public-corpus skill exceptions",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR now documents the trust boundary for curated public-corpus skill exceptions without adding an installable skill fixture.\n\n- keeps direct skill additions rejected unless maintainers explicitly approve the curated public-corpus exception\n- documents the exception criteria and required evidence in `specs/dev-seeding.md`\n- clarifies that public-corpus dummy seeded owners are fixture-local and not publisher provenance\n- removes the proposed `coe-root-cause` corpus row/readable fixture/sync test from this PR, so no skill bypasses owner-scoped publishing\n\n## Trust / security impact\n\nNormal community or publisher skills must still use the authenticated owner-scoped publish path. A committed public-corpus skill fixture is only allowed when maintainers explicitly approve the exception and the PR includes readable source, sync proof, validation, and rationale.\n\nThis branch no longer lands `coe-root-cause` as public-corpus content. It only records the policy needed for maintainers to evaluate future curated fixture exceptions.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `bun run validate:public-corpus`\n- `bun test scripts/public-corpus/validate.test.ts scripts/public-corpus/seed-public-corpus.test.ts`\n- `bun run ci:static`\n",
